                    "action_type": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "action_type",
                        "name": "Two Actions"
                    },
                    "frequency": "once per day",
                    "effect": "You ring the bell and create an illusory image of a delicious-looking banquet of food laid out on an altar in a 5-foot-square at any point within 30 feet of you that you can see. Any creature that must eat food to survive that's within 30 feet of the appearance of the illusory food must succeed at a DC 28 Will save or be so distracted by the food's sight and smell that they become fascinated by it for 10 minutes. This food's appearance can trigger any jiang-shi's Bitter Epiphany weakness; if the food does so, the jiang-shi takes a \u20132 item penalty to its Will save to resist the effects of this weakness.",
                    "traits": [
                        {
                            "name": "Olfactory",
                            "type": "trait",
                            "alternate_link": {
